Installation:
1) Copy files to appropriate locations, check paths in scripts

/etc/zabbix/externalscripts: (zabbix scripts)
 svc_perf (chmod +x)
 svc_perf_discovery (chmod +x)
 svc_perf_discovery.py
 svc_perf_wbem.py

/etc/cron.d: (statistics polling script)
 svc_perf_cron

/var/cache/zabbix: (script-created cache files, must be persistent, rw access for zabbix user)
 svc_perf.XXX.cache
 svc_perf.XXX.errlog

2) Import template to Zabbix from file _Special_Storwize_Perf.xml
3) Create node with DNS name/IP address pointing to Storwize BLOCK module mgmt interface, link template _Special_Storwize_Perf
4) Wait some time - Zabbix will call discovery script and add items to node
5) Cron will periodically run collect script and feed stats to Zabbix
